comment_regular_data.body:
@zeertzjq

I looked at that section of code and that does look like the right place to put this expansion to fix the problem I am trying to solve. But I wonder, do we want this expansion for only file arguments or for any file handling in general, e.g. from vimscript, ex commands, etc.. I think the latter behavior would be nicer, because then I can do e.g. `:e ~/.ssh/config` and it would work as well.

Your thoughts please.
